1
00:00:10,367 --> 00:00:11,533
<i> I'm easy to talk to.</i>

2
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:14,467
<i>Let's close this
at twenty thousand!</i>

3
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:18,033
<i> Amo! Amo!</i>

4
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:18,900
<i> Get Down!</i>

5
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:23,233
<i> Enriquez, backstage!</i>

6
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:24,267
<i> Are you okay?</i>

7
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,533
<i>Shut up, Victor!
We know you did this!</i>

8
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:29,900
<i>None of you is the sniper's
target.</i>

9
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:30,667
<i> Then who?</i>

10
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:31,867
<i> I think Selena is the target.</i>

11
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,367
<i>Surround the perimeter!
The shooter is still there!</i>

12
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,467
<i> Hey, Sir, do you need help?</i>

13
00:00:34,633 --> 00:00:36,567
<i> Yes, there's an exit.</i>

14
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:38,233
<i>Sir, we've checked
the entire area.</i>

15
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:39,700
<i>It looks like the sniper
has escaped.</i>

16
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:43,267
<i>Sergeant Enriquez and
Lieutenant Conde will take you</i>

17
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,700
<i>and accompany you to the
safehouse for the time being.</i>

18
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:46,867
<i> I tripped on my foot earlier.</i>

19
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,767
<i> Ouch, it hurts.</i>

20
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:49,700
<i> Oh my, it's pissing me off!</i>

21
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:51,433
<i> Bautista, can I have that?</i>

22
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:52,733
<i> Ouch, ouch, ouch.</i>

23
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:54,267
<i> Sir, I'll leave you.</i>

24
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,867
<i> Where are you going?</i>

25
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,033
<i>I'm just here,
I'm just here.</i>

26
00:00:58,667 --> 00:01:00,300
<i>Just a little,
just a little.</i>

27
00:01:00,967 --> 00:01:01,867
<i> Ouch, Ouch.</i>

28
00:01:04,567 --> 00:01:05,600
Grandmother,

29
00:01:05,733 --> 00:01:10,433
can you pack me my sleeping
garments and toiletries?

30
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:12,967
Then can you please bring me
here to the precinct?

31
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:15,633
Here it is, it's all ready.

32
00:01:15,767 --> 00:01:17,500
Be careful, Grandchild.

33
00:01:17,633 --> 00:01:20,367
Maybe you'll be the one
targeted by the gunman.

34
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:22,200
Couldn't someone else
be the one to escort?

35
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:24,900
Oh no, that's not going
to happen.

36
00:01:25,033 --> 00:01:29,867
I can handle that besides,
Sir Tonyo is with me.

37
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,167
Tonyo?

38
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:32,633
Are you with Tonyo?

39
00:01:32,767 --> 00:01:35,000
Wait, I'll change your sleeping
garment.

40
00:01:36,467 --> 00:01:37,600
Look at this, Grandmother.

41
00:01:37,733 --> 00:01:40,800
You just found out that
I'm with Sir Tonyo,

42
00:01:40,967 --> 00:01:42,067
and you suddenly changed.

43
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:44,500
So you can bond!

44
00:01:44,633 --> 00:01:48,700
If you want, you can live there.
I'll send all your stuff.

45
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:51,767
Grandmother is giving me away.

46
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:53,567
Really, it's just work,
Grandmother.

47
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:56,867
Besides, it looks like he wants
to bond with someone else.

48
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:58,467
then who?

49
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:00,667
Nothing.

50
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,233
Go ahead, Grandmother.

51
00:02:02,367 --> 00:02:04,267
Please send them over, okay?

52
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,067
Yes, okay. Okay,
I'll take care of it.

53
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,300
Thank you, Grandmother.

54
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:08,233
Bye.

55
00:02:08,367 --> 00:02:10,267
Mar, Abdul!

56
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:13,400
Kapitana!

57
00:02:14,733 --> 00:02:15,433
Why?

58
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:16,467
Come on.

59
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:18,600
You're going to take this
to my grandchild.

60
00:02:19,733 --> 00:02:21,733
Okay, Kapitana. We'll take it.

61
00:02:21,867 --> 00:02:22,933
Yes, to the precinct.

62
00:02:23,067 --> 00:02:24,300
Kapitana...

63
00:02:24,433 --> 00:02:27,300
Mar and I had an idea.

64
00:02:27,433 --> 00:02:31,433
Kapitana, aren't we in danger
here?

65
00:02:31,567 --> 00:02:34,267
Well, we should move to
a different house first,

66
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,567
especially since the gunman
hasn't been caught yet.

67
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:40,033
You're right,
we're in danger here.

68
00:02:41,233 --> 00:02:42,700
I know a house.

69
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,233
There, there you go.

70
00:02:45,367 --> 00:02:46,233
Okay, okay.

71
00:02:46,367 --> 00:02:47,600
Take that to my grandchild.

72
00:02:47,767 --> 00:02:49,833
Okay.

73
00:02:49,967 --> 00:02:50,700
You carry that, okay?

74
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:51,567
Okay.

75
00:02:55,033 --> 00:02:56,867
Hey, stay here.

76
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,067
I'm going out.

77
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:58,933
No.

78
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:02,133
You stay here.

79
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:04,600
You can't just go inside
and kill the target.

80
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:06,400
See?

81
00:03:06,533 --> 00:03:08,267
It's a police station.

82
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,200
No.

83
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:11,000
I don't wait for anyone.

84
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:15,300
This guy is crazy. Hey! Hey!

85
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,300
This guy is crazy.

86
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:22,033
He's hard to talk to,
and he is stubborn.

87
00:03:51,967 --> 00:03:53,267
What are you doing here?

88
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:56,067
Get out.

89
00:03:57,433 --> 00:04:00,100
Don't tell me what to do.

90
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,833
I go my way.

91
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:13,400
Sir Tonyo, maybe I can go use
the CR first.

92
00:04:15,767 --> 00:04:17,167
Upstairs, Ma'am Selena.

93
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,133
I'll just go with her, Sir.

94
00:04:20,267 --> 00:04:21,200
Okay.

95
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:22,133
Bok.

96
00:05:10,133 --> 00:05:10,867
What did you do inside?

97
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:16,333
I wanted to see the police who
anticipated my shot a while ago.

98
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:21,233
I just want to know who he is,
how he moves,

99
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:24,733
because I want him dead too.

100
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:41,333
Bok, these are Ma'am Selena's
things.

101
00:05:42,367 --> 00:05:45,733
I've already chosen the freshest
ones.

102
00:05:45,867 --> 00:05:46,733
Thank you, Bok.

103
00:05:46,867 --> 00:05:48,567
We'll go ahead.
Let's go, Enriquez.

104
00:06:03,467 --> 00:06:04,467
Follow them.

105
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:20,433
Miss Selena, are you okay?

106
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:25,133
Is it really safe where we're
going?

107
00:06:25,267 --> 00:06:26,467
Yes, it's safe there.

108
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,433
No one knows about it but us.

109
00:06:28,567 --> 00:06:30,700
And we, are we safe?

110
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:33,067
Maybe they'll follow us later,

111
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,933
or maybe they'll be waiting
there.

112
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:38,267
Don't worry, Miss Selena.

113
00:06:38,767 --> 00:06:40,533
Enriquez is on the lookout.

114
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,767
She's like an owl.

115
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:44,233
Owl?

116
00:06:44,367 --> 00:06:45,433
Are my eyes big?

117
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:50,767
That's not what I meant.
What I meant was alert, focused.

118
00:06:51,267 --> 00:06:52,267
It's good that it's clear.

119
00:06:54,167 --> 00:06:56,033
This bulletproof...

120
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:58,167
This is really bulletproof,
isn't it?

121
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:02,900
What if, for example,
I get shot, won't I get hurt?

122
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:05,133
I'm sorry, I have so many
questions.

123
00:07:05,267 --> 00:07:07,433
I'm just nervous.

124
00:07:07,567 --> 00:07:09,633
Just relax, Miss Selena.

125
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,600
I don't seem to see anyone
following us.

126
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,500
Tere...

127
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,667
Yes?

128
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,967
I would have dropped you off,

129
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:29,433
but we're busy here
at the office.

130
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:30,700
That's fine, Uncle.

131
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:33,300
It's a great help that you
talked to the person you know

132
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:34,367
at the job fair.

133
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:36,633
And Kaloy and I can commute,
right?

134
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:37,967
Hey, wait!

135
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:39,167
What a waste.

136
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:41,967
I thought I'd be able
to get my fare for free.

137
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:42,867
That's okay.

138
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,167
I called my contact
at the job fair.

139
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:46,700
Submit your resume.

140
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:47,733
He'll take care of you.

141
00:07:48,867 --> 00:07:49,600
I told you.

142
00:07:49,733 --> 00:07:52,267
And of course,
I'll pay for your fare.

143
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:53,967
Uncle, no need.

144
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:55,067
Promise, we can manage.

145
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,233
- It's okay. Go ahead.
- Thank you, thank you.

146
00:07:56,367 --> 00:07:58,033
Just take good care of Tere.

147
00:07:58,167 --> 00:08:00,867
Oh, yes, Sir!
I won't neglect her, Sir.

148
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,067
Okay.

149
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,733
If there's a problem,
call me, okay?

150
00:08:03,867 --> 00:08:04,833
Yes, copy, Sir.

151
00:08:04,967 --> 00:08:05,833
- Thank you.
- Thank you, Uncle.

152
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:06,267
Be careful.

153
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,400
Okay.

154
00:08:07,767 --> 00:08:08,567
We'll go ahead. Bye.

155
00:08:14,167 --> 00:08:14,433
Hey.

156
00:08:15,867 --> 00:08:17,367
Why are you seated there?

157
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:19,367
Because I'm your boss.

158
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:20,900
In your dreams.

159
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:23,000
Just drive.

160
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:24,900
I'm unlucky, aren't I?

161
00:08:25,033 --> 00:08:28,033
I've had a boyfriend once,
and he's a criminal.

162
00:08:28,167 --> 00:08:30,400
Now I'm also involved.

163
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:32,833
There's a reason for everything,
Miss Selena.

164
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:39,367
And you, Enriquez, don't you
plan on having a boyfriend?

165
00:08:40,767 --> 00:08:44,533
Well, if it's just like hers,
never mind.

166
00:08:44,667 --> 00:08:46,833
Of course,
I want a sensible man.

167
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:48,933
A policeman is fine.

168
00:08:52,467 --> 00:08:55,000
I didn't say I wanted
a policeman, Sir.

169
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,300
Just drive there, Sir.

170
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,067
Hey, can you move closer?

171
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,533
We're getting too far from them.

172
00:09:18,667 --> 00:09:21,333
No, the police might notice
that we are tailing them.

173
00:09:21,467 --> 00:09:22,167
Why?

174
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:24,633
So I can shoot them from behind.

175
00:09:24,767 --> 00:09:26,233
That's too risky.

176
00:09:26,367 --> 00:09:28,133
We are in a moving vehicle,

177
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:31,267
and we don't even know where
Selena is in those cars,

178
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:34,100
and this highway has a lot
of CCTV cameras.

179
00:09:34,233 --> 00:09:37,467
The plan is we follow them
until they reach the safe house.

180
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:40,133
And from there,
we'll finish our job.

181
00:09:40,267 --> 00:09:43,033
Oh, no, no, no,
that's too long.

182
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,400
This guy is really crazy.

183
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:46,367
What did you say?

184
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:51,200
I said Don't make unnecessary
movements.

185
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:52,633
You're arrogant.

186
00:09:54,067 --> 00:09:57,300
Sir Tonyo, can we pass by
a store,

187
00:09:57,433 --> 00:10:00,400
maybe I can buy something.

188
00:10:02,733 --> 00:10:03,900
Thank you.

189
00:10:16,267 --> 00:10:16,967
They separated.

190
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,200
Which car are we going
to follow?

191
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:20,600
Okay, the one in the middle.
Go straight.

192
00:10:20,733 --> 00:10:23,267
No, we go right.

193
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:26,300
I said go straight! Why?

194
00:10:26,433 --> 00:10:29,067
Cause I'm the Captain here!
I'm holding the wheel!

195
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:38,333
- Hey! Hey!
- Go ahead, drive!

196
00:10:38,467 --> 00:10:40,333
Hey, roll down the window!

197
00:10:40,467 --> 00:10:41,600
Are you going to kill us?

198
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:42,733
You're an idiot!

199
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:44,967
It's your fault,
you're not looking!

200
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:45,967
You idiot!

201
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:48,300
Thank goodness I have work,
I'm in a hurry.

202
00:10:48,433 --> 00:10:49,133
Get down!

203
00:10:49,267 --> 00:10:50,400
Get out of your car!

204
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:02,833
Stoplight.

205
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:05,233
See?

206
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:06,800
There's the third car.

207
00:11:06,933 --> 00:11:07,933
I told you.

208
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:10,733
Okay.

209
00:11:10,867 --> 00:11:12,400
I will finish them now.

210
00:11:14,367 --> 00:11:15,967
Be ready to escape.

211
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,233
What's that?

212
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:46,033
Sorry, wrong car. Nothing.

213
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:01,133
We've been following a different
car all this time!

214
00:12:01,267 --> 00:12:02,867
So what now, huh?

215
00:12:03,167 --> 00:12:04,500
We lost them!

216
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:06,900
It's your fault.

217
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:10,700
It's okay.

218
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:12,267
We will find them.

219
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:30,733
Wow.

220
00:12:30,867 --> 00:12:32,500
There are a lot of jobs here.

221
00:12:32,633 --> 00:12:36,400
Yes, but the question is,
will our qualifications fit?

222
00:12:36,533 --> 00:12:37,167
What?

223
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:38,767
Qualifications.
You're perfect?

224
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:40,133
Do you know what you're talking
about?

225
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:41,833
That's why we're here, right?

226
00:12:41,967 --> 00:12:44,933
For us to find out what kind
of work is right for us.

227
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:48,300
What else are we waiting for?

228
00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:50,467
Let the job hunting begin!

229
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,533
Game, game.

230
00:12:52,667 --> 00:12:54,333
Wait, wait, wait.

231
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:55,967
What? There you are again.

232
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:58,167
My stomach is upset.

233
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,267
What? Now, really?

234
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,667
I feel like doing a number two.

235
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,000
You're always like that.

236
00:13:02,133 --> 00:13:05,333
I'm really like this, right,
when I'm nervous?

237
00:13:05,467 --> 00:13:08,400
As long as the plan is,
after you're done with that.

238
00:13:08,533 --> 00:13:10,267
Yes, okay. Okay.

239
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,333
Hurry up, okay?

240
00:13:11,467 --> 00:13:13,633
Miss, I need this.
Thank you very much, okay.

241
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:16,767
Excuse me, excuse me.

242
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:18,700
Ladies Room.

243
00:13:33,667 --> 00:13:35,133
Kaloy's taking too long.

244
00:13:41,267 --> 00:13:43,200
Miss, let me take a picture.

245
00:13:50,767 --> 00:13:53,167
Miss, Miss, let me take a
picture.

246
00:14:14,467 --> 00:14:17,600
Hi, Miss. can I take a picture
of you?

247
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,167
Are you going to post
that on social media?

248
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:22,300
No, we won't.

249
00:14:22,433 --> 00:14:23,933
It's just for our file,

250
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:26,567
so that if we find
a good job for you.

251
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:28,200
We can easily contact you.

252
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:29,400
Job?

253
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,933
Yes.

254
00:14:32,067 --> 00:14:35,967
Is that like a resume,
and then you guys start looking,

255
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,200
you'll contact me, right?

256
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:38,400
Yes, it's like that.

257
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:39,500
What? Game?

258
00:14:39,633 --> 00:14:41,900
Yes, okay. Make it good, Okay?

259
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:43,867
Our booth is over there.
Let's go there.

260
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Okay.

261
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:55,800
What? Get down there!

262
00:14:55,933 --> 00:14:57,400
What's going on?

263
00:14:57,700 --> 00:15:00,333
Damn, this is the one who was
acting stupid earlier!

264
00:15:00,467 --> 00:15:01,767
Aren't you brave?

265
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,500
You're so arrogant!

266
00:15:05,633 --> 00:15:06,100
Is he the one?

267
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:07,233
Yes, he's the brave guy.

268
00:15:07,367 --> 00:15:08,900
You even called for backup.
You think I'm scared?

269
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:10,233
You will be really scared!

270
00:15:12,133 --> 00:15:13,467
You are arrogant!

271
00:15:19,433 --> 00:15:20,567
Stupid.

272
00:16:01,467 --> 00:16:02,767
Anyone else?

273
00:16:05,767 --> 00:16:07,233
I told you I can manage.

274
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:10,533
The police will find us!

275
00:16:10,667 --> 00:16:13,100
Is this Filipino for thank you?

276
00:16:13,233 --> 00:16:15,033
You wake up! Let's go!

277
00:16:30,567 --> 00:16:35,167
Sir, hurry, okay?
We shouldn't be stopping, right?

278
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:39,067
I'm sorry, I just need some
alcohol.

279
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:42,067
Never mind, I'll do it.
Just a second.

280
00:16:54,933 --> 00:16:57,567
Ma'am Bobby, you're great,
aren't you?

281
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:59,533
You managed to become
a police officer.

282
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,067
Can I ask a question?

283
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:07,233
Don't you like Sir Tonyo?

284
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:08,567
Tonyo?

285
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:13,533
Can I ask a question?

286
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,700
Don't you have a type
for Sir Tonyo?

287
00:17:17,167 --> 00:17:18,367
Tonyo?

288
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:23,033
Oh my, I don't even like
the tip of his fingernail.

289
00:17:23,367 --> 00:17:24,367
Really?

290
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:25,933
Seriously.

291
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:28,633
If I were with Sir Tonyo
every day,

292
00:17:28,767 --> 00:17:30,300
I would fall for him.

293
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,400
You'll fall for him right away?

294
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:38,600
Miss Selena, you should get
to know the person well

295
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:41,967
before you commit
to something serious.

296
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:45,233
Besides, you shouldn't give in
to those thrills.

297
00:17:45,367 --> 00:17:47,533
You should be with the sensible
one,

298
00:17:47,667 --> 00:17:49,267
the one who won't leave you.

299
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:51,267
Well, you have a point.

300
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,600
Wait for a while.

301
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:21,467
Tere, right?

302
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,467
- Yes, Tere.
- Have a drink first.

303
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:24,600
Thank you.

304
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:25,600
Okay, let me just set up here,
okay?

305
00:18:25,733 --> 00:18:26,400
Okay.

306
00:18:29,867 --> 00:18:31,633
Sorry, what's your name again?

307
00:18:31,767 --> 00:18:32,700
Chris.

308
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:33,500
Chris.

309
00:18:35,967 --> 00:18:39,467
Chris, make me look good, okay?
I really need a job.

310
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,933
I won't have any trouble making
you look good

311
00:18:41,067 --> 00:18:41,833
because you're really pretty.

312
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:43,400
Come on, he's such a sweet
talker.

313
00:18:43,533 --> 00:18:46,867
I don't need any sweet talk,
I need a job.

314
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,800
So make me look good, okay?

315
00:18:50,867 --> 00:18:52,000
Okay, drink that.

316
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:54,500
Okay. Thank you.

317
00:19:14,967 --> 00:19:16,567
Sir, are you going to apply?

318
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:17,567
Yes.

319
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:18,500
Do you have an opening?

320
00:19:18,633 --> 00:19:21,533
Yes. These are our hiring
positions.

321
00:19:25,767 --> 00:19:26,933
There's just too much
to choose from.

322
00:19:27,067 --> 00:19:28,700
Would you like me to orient you?

323
00:19:30,933 --> 00:19:33,933
Okay, but I'll use the CR first.

324
00:19:34,067 --> 00:19:36,000
- Okay.
- I'll be back.

325
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,067
Thank you.

326
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:41,733
Just a moment.

327
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:45,033
Thank you.

328
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:45,733
Okay.

329
00:19:45,867 --> 00:19:46,767
Thank you.

330
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:49,167
We have to leave, let's go.

331
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:50,767
They say our colleagues
got into trouble

332
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:52,833
at the corner of Milagros.

333
00:19:52,967 --> 00:19:55,500
They said the man from
the SUV shot them.

334
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:57,367
Junior is dead!

335
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,300
Poor Junior.

336
00:19:59,433 --> 00:20:00,933
Come on, let's respond.

337
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:03,267
It's not our job to respond,
Enriquez.

338
00:20:03,433 --> 00:20:04,967
That's out of our jurisdiction.

339
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:05,767
Let's go.

340
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:07,133
But, Sir, we need to help those
people.

341
00:20:07,267 --> 00:20:09,433
Enriquez, let's just report
that to the station.

342
00:20:09,567 --> 00:20:10,733
They'll take care of that.

343
00:20:10,867 --> 00:20:14,000
Our job now is to take Selena
to the safehouse.

344
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:14,900
Let's go.

345
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,267
What, are you ready?

346
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,267
Yes, okay.

347
00:20:35,433 --> 00:20:36,567
Is it okay?

348
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:37,467
Let's go.

349
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,067
Can I put it here?

350
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:47,567
Are you okay?

351
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:49,567
Are you okay?

352
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:53,767
I'm just a little dizzy.

353
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:57,333
Wait, have you eaten?

354
00:20:57,467 --> 00:20:58,367
Yeah.

355
00:20:58,500 --> 00:21:02,133
You know, its better let's go
to the medic.

356
00:21:02,267 --> 00:21:03,733
I saw something outside.

357
00:21:03,867 --> 00:21:05,367
No, no, no, I'm okay.

358
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,067
I'm okay.

359
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:08,967
Are you sure?

360
00:21:11,667 --> 00:21:12,500
Oh, okay.

361
00:21:12,633 --> 00:21:14,467
Okay, okay, let's go.

362
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:14,933
Okay.

363
00:21:15,067 --> 00:21:15,567
Game.

364
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:21,167
I told you.

365
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:23,233
Come on, let's go there.

366
00:21:23,367 --> 00:21:24,200
Ah, wait, my bag.

367
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:26,333
Oh, is that it? Okay, let me.

368
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:29,833
Just a moment.

369
00:21:39,133 --> 00:21:41,333
The medic is here.

370
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,633
Let's go, for...

371
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:44,400
Hurry up.

372
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:51,633
Tere?

373
00:21:52,767 --> 00:21:53,567
Tere!

374
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:56,933
Tere?

375
00:21:57,067 --> 00:21:57,800
Hey!

376
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:59,733
Where are you taking my friend?

377
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:17,467
Where are you taking my friend?

378
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:18,600
Take him with you!

379
00:22:18,733 --> 00:22:19,600
He might interfere!

380
00:22:19,733 --> 00:22:20,733
Hey!

381
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:25,333
Hurry up! Let's go.

382
00:22:31,967 --> 00:22:32,767
Stop!

383
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,133
Come in.

384
00:22:56,267 --> 00:22:57,933
Okay, I just finished cleaning.

385
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:00,833
Come in.

386
00:23:00,967 --> 00:23:01,867
Thank you.

387
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,900
Tomorrow,
I'll cook lunch for you.

388
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:12,333
I'm Erning.

389
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:15,933
My place is near the market.

390
00:23:18,567 --> 00:23:20,667
Sir, this is my son's number.

391
00:23:21,867 --> 00:23:25,500
I'm a little hard of hearing,
so I have a hearing aid.

392
00:23:25,633 --> 00:23:27,033
I also take it off at night.

393
00:23:27,167 --> 00:23:31,733
Then sometimes it breaks,
so I really can't hear anything.

394
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:34,200
Just call him if you need
anything.

395
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:37,833
Yes, Sir, there's a room
here for you to sleep in,

396
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:39,533
and then here too.

397
00:23:39,667 --> 00:23:41,300
That's the living room,
you can sleep in there too.

398
00:23:41,433 --> 00:23:43,400
I'll go ahead, Sir.

399
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:45,400
- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you, Erning!

400
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:52,267
Ma'am Bobby, Sir Tonyo,
come on, let's chill.

401
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:56,133
Let's celebrate that we made it
here alive.

402
00:23:57,533 --> 00:24:01,033
Selena, you better rest.

403
00:24:01,167 --> 00:24:05,733
Come on, Ma'am, so we can relax.

404
00:24:05,867 --> 00:24:08,367
I almost died earlier.

405
00:24:08,700 --> 00:24:10,467
I'm sorry, I can't.

406
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:15,600
Come on, Ma'am. Just one.
It's already late.

407
00:24:15,733 --> 00:24:18,000
You know,
alcohol really helps me,

408
00:24:18,133 --> 00:24:21,567
especially in situations
like this.

409
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:26,333
It takes away my anxiety,
and I can relax.

410
00:24:26,467 --> 00:24:29,433
I'm just babbling a little,

411
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:35,033
but it's better than being
nervous.

412
00:24:37,733 --> 00:24:39,067
Maybe that's okay, just one.

413
00:24:40,667 --> 00:24:43,067
Sir, are you going to drink?

414
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:46,633
Just one.

415
00:24:46,767 --> 00:24:48,767
That's not possible for us, Sir.

416
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:58,433
Okay, stop me.

417
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,667
I said give me that.

418
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:33,467
The assigned officers are on
their way to escort you, Selena.

419
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:36,067
So, when they get here,
are you leaving?

420
00:25:36,233 --> 00:25:37,100
They're the cops

421
00:25:37,233 --> 00:25:39,267
who will replace the escorts
of our target.

422
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:42,100
Let's wait for them to finish,
and then we'll move.

423
00:25:42,233 --> 00:25:43,500
His face is similar to...

424
00:25:43,633 --> 00:25:46,833
He looks like our mysterious
oppa, man.

425
00:25:46,967 --> 00:25:47,767
Is that him?

426
00:25:47,900 --> 00:25:50,533
Don't you know my ex, Sonny?

427
00:25:50,667 --> 00:25:52,367
Sir, what are you doing?
